  "text": "We have shown in this article that graphs with a scale-free degree distribution appear naturally as the result of a simple edge formation rule based on choices where the probability to chose a vertex with characteristic ω is proportional to the frequency of appearance of that characteristic. If the affinity parameter ω is itself power law like distributed one could also use a direct proportionality to the value ω to get still a scale free graph since ϕ (ω) is itself a polynomial relation (this explains the observation reported in [CITATION_1] ).",
